snippet.textDisplay:
The word rapping  comes from West African griot tradition. And it later used in hip hop singing, which is in English. So there is no point making or mixing it with Indian classical or any other Indian music. And to you Raftaar, if you really want to make something in rapping, why don't you sing it in English, which is it's orginal language. Then everyone will know how much talent you have. 
Take some tips from Gurdass mann, Sukhwinder Singh. They never needed any other languages to show their skills except their own language (Punjabi).
